            <title><![CDATA[School Visits]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[<article><h1>School Visits</h1><p>Hundreds of years ago, being an author meant you sat in a stuffy little room called a garret with an ink pot and paper and a mug of ale or something, and you wrote. You wrote your books, and then after a few years you died of smallpox or something and you didn’t get famous and read by millions of people until hundreds of years afterwards.</p><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/the-grid-img/p/cc99ccba3f9dd0da2f06db752ad855bcbcf8a64a.jpg"></article>]]></description>
